					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1324229"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1445261354 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Oct 2015 13:29</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2393793">
									

<p>I really like this and am surprised that it's rated so low. I think that, despite five years for other interpretations to take root, this is still one of the foundational (heh) documents for Marshall, Carter, and Dark as individual characters, rather than &quot;faceless evil aristocrats&quot; (the other two being <a href="/taking-stock">Taking Stock</a> and <a href="/thank-you-for-your-time">Thank You For Your Time</a>).</p>
<p>However, looking back on it, I am a bit weirded out by the random blackboxing. That's more a Foundation flourish, but the letter is, in-story at least, being read by Marshall and Carter. It seems like it's being used for &quot;mysterious information goes here&quot; but in a way that makes no sense for the story.</p>
<p>Still, letter!Dark is best Dark, and it's always a pleasure to stumble upon this. +1</p>

							</div>

								
